label: categoryCode
comment: A code specifying a category for this cross-border regulatory procedure, such as the appendices of the CITES Convention.
A code specifying a category for this document authentication.
A code specifying a category for this specified certificate.
A code specifying a category for this transport person, such as a member of crew or passenger.
A code specifying a category of this government registration.
The code specifying a category for this exchanged document.
The code specifying the category for this fault.
The code specifying the category for this logistics risk analysis result.
The code specifying the category for this pet animal.
The code specifying the category for this specified assessment.
The code specifying the category for this specified experience item.
The code specifying the category for this specified object.
The code specifying the category for this water source.
The code specifying the category of disease protection means.
The code specifying the category of this certified accreditation, such as driving or academic.
The code specifying the category of this document line.
The code specifying the category of this experience product.
The code specifying the category of this product label.
The code specifying the category of this referenced document.
The code specifying the category of this specified information source.
The code specifying the category of this subordinate trade line item.
The code specifying the category of this sustainability characteristic.
The code specifying the category, such as adult or child, of this specified customer class,

domainIncludes.comment: A certified recognition that provides evidence of a level of competency in a given area, such as certifying a level of skill in a trade.
The evaluation of an object, such as a product, process, or organization, with respect to the object's worth or condition.
A proof that a document is genuine.
The conditions and requirements of the type of person who may use or purchase a product or service.
Written, printed or electronic matter that is referenced.
A collection of data for a line on a piece of written, printed or electronic matter that provides information or evidence.
A collection of data for a piece of written, printed or electronic matter that is exchanged between two or more parties.
A collection of information specific to the involvement of a person or persons in a happening, such as a theme park, a guided tour being used or reported on for trade purposes.
Any service that provides an involvement, such as an adventure experience, wellness experience, social or business activity experience.
The recording of items or details for a governmental purpose.
A person, organization, thing or place from which information comes, arises or is obtained.
Anything that is visible or tangible, such as a product, process, or organization.
A domestic or tamed animal that is kept for companionship or pleasure.
A label, such as a garment label or a radio frequency tag, used for identifying a product.
A way to protect something, such as human beings, animals or environment, from getting infected or becoming ill.
A set of formal steps to satisfy a cross-border regulation, law or convention.
The result of a logistics risk analysis calculation.
A place from which water originates, such as a hot spring or lake that provides water to public drinking water supplies and private wells.
A document issued by a government, public organization or association to certify a property of a person, entity, process or object.
An unattractive or unsatisfactory characteristic.
A collection of information specific to a subordinate item being used or reported on for trade purposes.
A prominent attribute or aspect of an object, such as recyclability of a product, which can meet customer needs without compromising the ability of future generations to meet their own needs.
A transport related person, such as a member of a crew or a passenger.
